  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "Profitability metrics remained robust in Q4 2025, with gross margin at 59.82%, operating margin at 31.61%, and net margin at 30.25%. Operating income for the quarter totaled $36,002,000,000, while net income reached $34,455,000,000. These margin levels indicate Alphabet maintained strong pricing power and operational efficiency despite continued investments in infrastructure and AI capabilities. The EBITDA margin of 39.91% further underscores the company's cash generation capacity from core operations.",
